ntent":"`Dockerfile.participant-hardened`"},"1124":{"id":"/docs/infrastructure/docker-23","page_id":"/docs/infrastructure/docker","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/infrastructure/docker#with-docker-compose","content":"Runs participant code with flopscope-client only"},"1125":{"id":"/docs/infrastructure/docker-24","page_id":"/docs/infrastructure/docker","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/infrastructure/docker#with-docker-compose","content":"The containers share an IPC socket volume for communication."},"1126":{"id":"/docs/infrastructure/docker-25","page_id":"/docs/infrastructure/docker","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/infrastructure/docker#without-docker","content":"From a source checkout, start both processes from the repository root so the\nserver can import the local `src/flopscope` package:"},"1127":{"id":"/docs/infrastructure/docker-26","page_id":"/docs/infrastructure/docker","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/infrastructure/docker#without-docker","content":"For TCP (e.g., across machines):"},"1128":{"id":"/docs/infrastructure/docker-27","page_id":"/docs/infrastructure/docker","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/infrastructure/docker#without-docker","content":"If you already have `flopscope-client` and `flopscope-server` installed into\nseparate environments, the shorter `cd ... && uv run ...` workflow also works.\nThe commands above are the reproducible source-checkout path."},"1129":{"id":"/docs/infrastructure/docker-28","page_id":"/docs/infrastructure/docker","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/infrastructure/docker#time-limit-enforcement","content":"Submissions run under two layers of time enforcement:"},"1130":{"id":"/docs/infrastructure/docker-29","page_id":"/docs/infrastructure/docker","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/infrastructure/docker#time-limit-enforcement","content":"**In-library (cooperative):** `BudgetContext(wall_time_limit_s=N)` checks the deadline before and after each numpy call. When exceeded, it raises `TimeExhaustedError` with diagnostic info (which operation, elapsed time, configured limit). This is a UX feature — it gives participants a clean error message."},"1131":{"id":"/docs/infrastructure/docker-30","page_id":"/docs/infrastructure/docker","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/infrastructure/docker#time-limit-enforcement","content":"**Container-level (hard):** The Docker container enforces a kernel-level time limit via cgroups/rlimit. If the in-library check doesn't catch the overshoot (e.g., a single very long numpy call), the container delivers `SIGKILL`. This is the ultimate backstop — no Python code can escape it."},"1132":{"id":"/docs/infrastructure/docker-31","page_id":"/docs/infrastructure/docker","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/infrastructure/docker#time-limit-enforcement","content":"Signal-based preemption (`SIGALRM`) is deliberately not used because Python signal handlers cannot interrupt C extensions (numpy/LAPACK/BLAS), making them ineffective for exactly the operations where time limits matter most."},"1133":{"id":"/docs/infrastructure/docker-32","page_id":"/docs/infrastructure/docker","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/infrastructure/docker#common-pitfalls","content":"**Symptom:** `Connection refused` or `timeout`"},"1134":{"id":"/docs/infrastructure/docker-33","page_id":"/docs/infrastructure/docker","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/infrastructure/docker#common-pitfalls","content":"**Fix:** Ensure the server is running before starting the client. Check that `FLOPSCOPE_SERVER_URL` matches the server's `--url` argument."},"1135":{"id":"/docs/infrastructure/docker-34","page_id":"/docs/infrastructure/docker","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/infrastructure/docker#common-pitfalls","content":"**Symptom:** Port conflict"},"1136":{"id":"/docs/infrastructure/docker-35","page_id":"/docs/infrastructure/docker","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/infrastructure/docker#common-pitfalls","content":"**Fix:** Change the port in both the server `--url` and client `FL