ing-model","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/understanding/flop-counting-model#how-costs-are-computed","content":"The cost is checked against the remaining budget"},"1175":{"id":"/docs/understanding/flop-counting-model-35","page_id":"/docs/understanding/flop-counting-model","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/understanding/flop-counting-model#how-costs-are-computed","content":"If within budget: the operation executes and the cost is deducted"},"1176":{"id":"/docs/understanding/flop-counting-model-36","page_id":"/docs/understanding/flop-counting-model","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/understanding/flop-counting-model#how-costs-are-computed","content":"If over budget: `BudgetExhaustedError` is raised, the operation does **not** execute"},"1177":{"id":"/docs/understanding/flop-counting-model-37","page_id":"/docs/understanding/flop-counting-model","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/understanding/flop-counting-model#cost-formulas-by-category","content":"Each formula below gives the **analytical base cost**. In normal use,\nflopscope loads the packaged official per-operation\nweights automatically at import time, so the base\ncost is multiplied by the operation's weight to give the final deducted\ncost. Set `FLOPSCOPE_DISABLE_WEIGHTS=1` if you want the pure analytical unit-cost\nmodel instead."},"1178":{"id":"/docs/understanding/flop-counting-model-38","page_id":"/docs/understanding/flop-counting-model","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/understanding/flop-counting-model#cost-formulas-by-category","content":"Category"},"1179":{"id":"/docs/understanding/flop-counting-model-39","page_id":"/docs/understanding/flop-counting-model","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/understanding/flop-counting-model#cost-formulas-by-category","content":"Formula"},"1180":{"id":"/docs/understanding/flop-counting-model-40","page_id":"/docs/understanding/flop-counting-model","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/understanding/flop-counting-model#cost-formulas-by-category","content":"